---
title: "Order Refunded"
---
The **Order Refunded** trigger activates a flow when an order is marked as refunded in the system.

- **Note:** This Trigger is a part of [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce) Integration

- **Topics covered:** -
- [How to Configure Order Refunded Trigger](#how-to-configure-order-refunded-trigger)

- [Practical Example](#practical-example)

### How to Configure Order Refunded Trigger

While creating the Trigger Based Flows select **Order Refunded** trigger.

![mceclip0.png](./images/mceclip0-18.png)

When configuring the **Order Refunded** trigger, you'll need to complete the following steps:- **Name:** Give the trigger a clear, descriptive title to easily identify its function.

- **Description:** Provide a concise explanation of the trigger's purpose within the flow.

- **Select Store:** Choose the relevant BigCommerce store where the order refund process is being tracked.

- **Contact:** Specify any conditions based on customer details.

- **BigCommerce:** Define specific order-related conditions, like refund amount, reason for the refund, or other criteria to refine when the trigger is activated.Once the configuration is completed, hit **Save**.

![mceclip1.png](./images/mceclip1-18.png)
